===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|abatre||to abate}} + {{m|fro|-ment}}.<ref name = WI3>{{R:MW3 1976}}</ref>

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|legal}} The action of a person that abates, or without proper authority enters a residence after the death of the owner and before the heir takes possession.<ref name=WI3/>
# {{lb|en|legal}} The reduction of the proceeds of a will, when the debts have not yet been satisfied; the reduction of taxes due.<ref>{{R:RHCD|page=1}}</ref>{{defdate|First attested around 1150 to 1350.}}<ref name=SOED/>

